oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Copy print of John H. Jennings and his wife Martha E. Thomas Jennings
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This is a copy of a post-Civil War portrait of John H. Jennings and his wife Martha E. Thomas Jennings both of Decatur County, Tenn. John served as a sergeant in Co. C, 2nd Tenn. Mtd. Inf., USA. Martha's father served in the 52nd Tenn. Inf., CSA. John H. Jennings founded the Farmers Bank in Parsons, Tenn. after the war.
